The Controller & Hardware Engineering (CHE) team is part of the Intel Optane Group (IOG) business group within Intel that is responsible for the design, development, and verification of IntelÂ® Optaneâ„¢ based Persistent Memory and Solid State Drives (SSDs) for both client and enterprise applications. The CHE Hardware team is involved in all product phases ranging from product architecture, Printed Circuit Board (PCB) circuit design, mechanical enclosure design, simulations, layout, prototyping and validation leading to high volume manufacturing. 
Responsibilities include but are not limited to: 
Research, design, and develop mechanical and electromechanical devices or systems. 
Development of system concepts, conducting design previews, performing system acceptance, and resolving design and implementation issues. 
Responds to customer/client requests or events as they occur. 
Develops solutions to problems utilizing formal education and judgement. 
Soft Skills: 
Good verbal and written communications skills, in the form of test plans, reports and presentations. 
