Bachelorâ€™s degree in Mechanical Engineering or related field. 
Minimum Required Qualifications: 
4+ years of experience in the following areas:  Mechanical design and drafting with SolidWorks or Creo.  Applying heat transfer and structural analysis to product design.  Drafting and applying GDT to manufacturing drawings per ANSI Y14.5M standard.  Analyzing mechanical tolerance stacks using EXCEL, JMP, Crystal Ball or equivalent tools.  Designing products using one of the following fabrication processes: casting, extrusion, or stamping.  Product Data Management experience using Intel SPEED. 
 Additional Preferred Qualifications: 
 Â· 2+ years of experience independently creating design verification test plans and design-of-experiments.  2+ years performing CFD simulations using FloTherm, Icepak or similar software.  2+ years product data management using Windchill.  1+ years performing structural simulations using FEA tools such as ANSYS or ABAQUS.  Experience performing or directing shock and vibration testing of electronic packages.  Experience in PCB design and layout design rules using Cadence Allegro PCB.  Experience in mechanics of materials.  Experience in the application of DFMEA process.  Experience with creating project development plans and schedules.  Experience with managing multiple projects.
